I haue oft wondred howe fiſhes can retaine their freſh taſte, and yet liue in ſalt waters; ſince I ſee that euery other thing participates of the nature of the place, wherein it abides: ſo, the waters paſſing through
the chānels of the earth, varie their ſauour with the ve • nes of ſoyle, through vvhich they ſlide: So, brute creatures tranſported frō one Region to another, alter their former qualitie, & degenerate by little and little. The like daunger haue I ſeene in the manners of men, conuerſing with euill companions, in corrupt places: For, beſides that, it blemiſheth our reputation, and makes vs thought ill, though wee be good; it breedes in vs an inſenſible declination to ill;
and works in vs, if not an approbation, yet a leſſe diſlike of thoſe ſinnes, to which, our eares & eyes are ſo continually inured. I may haue a bad acquaintance, I will neuer haue a wicked companion.
